# Apple Design Skill (Chrome New Tab)

When reviewing or improving UI in this project, follow Apple Human Interface Guidelines principles adapted for a desktop browser new-tab page.

## Always check

- Accessibility: contrast ≥ 4.5:1 for body text, click targets ≥ 24px, do not rely on color alone
- Layout: clear hierarchy, consistent spacing, one job per section
- Color: semantic tokens (`--label`, `--surface`, `--accent`); support light and dark
- Typography: Outfit for Latin UI chrome; Hibur Mono for Ethiopic / Geez numerals
- Materials: subtle blur/surfaces sparingly; keep text legible over backgrounds
- Motion: purposeful, short; respect reduced motion when relevant

## Product-specific

- Calendar-first composition: clock/date + search as hero; grid and lists secondary
- Settled neutrals with soft teal accent — not Material You dynamic color, not purple gradients
- Bilingual EN/Amharic: Amharic strings use `.ethiopic` (Hibur Mono)

## Review output

Use severity: Critical / High / Medium / Low. Cite the principle and give a concrete CSS/React fix.
